  "response": "Here are some tips for asking out a girl from your college class:\n\n1. Start with friendly conversation\n- Talk to her before or after class\n- Ask about coursework or class-related topics\n- Build a casual rapport\n\n2. Gauge her interest\n- See if she seems comfortable talking with you\n- Notice if she appears engaged in the conversation\n- Look for signs she might be interested\n\n3. Consider asking her out casually\n- Suggest studying together\n- Invite her to a campus event\n- Ask if she'd like to grab coffee after class\n\n4. Be confident but respectful\n- Approach her politely\n- Be clear about your intentions\n- Accept gracefully if she declines\n\n5. Choose the right moment\n- When she's not rushed or stressed\n- In a semi-private setting\n- When you're both relaxed\n\n6. Keep it low-pressure\n- Suggest something casual like coffee\n- Give her an easy way to say no\n- Don't make her feel uncomfortable\n\nRemember, confidence and respect are key. Be yourself, and don't take rejection personally if it happens.",
